        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 17 at 4:27PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 427 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Follett, or 15 miles northeast of Lipscomb, moving north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Follett.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
